
**********************************************************************
This package contains working code and testbenches for doing gaussian
systemization on a random matrix.

Run the testbench in systemize_tb/ by invoking below command:

  ./run_test N L K

For example:

  ./run_test 4 8 16


Note:
Software Versions Used for Testing:
  SageMath (sage) 6.3 and 7.4
  Python (python) 2.7
  Icarus Verilog (iverilog) 0.9.7

**********************************************************************
For more explanations about the code, please refer to the paper:

Solving Large Systems of Linear Equations over GF(2) on FPGAs. 
Wen Wang, Jakub Szefer and Ruben Niederhagen. ReConFig, 2016.

**********************************************************************
For more information about the code/paper, please contact the authors:

Wen Wang -- wen.wang.ww349@yale.edu
Jakub Szefer -- jakub.szefer@yale.edu
Ruben Niederhagen -- ruben@polycephaly.org

